    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pens such as fountain pens and others that hold a reservoir of ink in the handle, holder, or other receptacle, as distinguished from dip pens that require frequent dipping of the pen point in ink, such as lettering pens, quill pens, reed pens, and others.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Schrijfpen met holle houder waarin zich een inktreservoir bevindt, in tegenstelling tot bijvoorbeeld kroontjespennen en ganzenpennen, die men regelmatig in de inkt moet dopen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>儲墨筆包括鋼筆或其他在把手、握柄或附帶盛器內設有儲墨槽的筆類。儲墨筆與沾水筆不同，因為後者須時常將筆尖浸入墨水中，例如繪圖水筆、羽毛筆、蘆葦筆等。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
